{
  "video_id": "jEXUG_vN540",
  "title": "How 'Spider-Man: Into The Spider-Verse' Was Animated | Movies Insider",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 3330.0,
      "end_time": 5150.0,
      "text": "Narrator: \"Spider-Man: Into The Spider-Verse\""
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 5150.0,
      "end_time": 7700.0,
      "text": "is no ordinary animated movie."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 7700.0,
      "end_time": 10590.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s no ordinary Spider-Man movie either."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 10590.0,
      "end_time": 12240.0,
      "text": "It packs multiple characters from"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 12240.0,
      "end_time": 15000.0,
      "text": "different universes into a seamless story,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 15000.0,
      "end_time": 18690.0,
      "text": "and it features an innovative, eye-grabbing animation style."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 18690.0,
      "end_time": 21300.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s that dedication to the animation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 21300.0,
      "end_time": 23680.0,
      "text": "a style we have never really seen before,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 23680.0,
      "end_time": 26463.0,
      "text": "that puts \"Spider-Verse\" in a category all its own."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 30490.0,
      "end_time": 32489.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s start with a few jaw-dropping"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 32490.000000000004,
      "end_time": 34310.0,
      "text": "numbers about the production."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 34310.0,
      "end_time": 39100.0,
      "text": "The film had 177 animators on staff at one point."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 39100.0,
      "end_time": 42600.0,
      "text": "More than twice the typical animated film."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 42600.0,
      "end_time": 44310.0,
      "text": "To put that in perspective, the original"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 44310.0,
      "end_time": 47420.0,
      "text": "\"Toy Story\" had just 27 animators."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 47420.0,
      "end_time": 51830.0,
      "text": "It took one week to animate just one second of footage."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 51830.0,
      "end_time": 54670.0,
      "text": "It usually takes a week for four seconds."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 54670.0,
      "end_time": 57290.0,
      "text": "It actually took them one year"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 57290.0,
      "end_time": 60160.0,
      "text": "to get just 10 seconds they were happy with."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 60160.0,
      "end_time": 61569.0,
      "text": "Peter B. Parker: Very cool."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 61570.0,
      "end_time": 63730.0,
      "text": "Narrator: And the total shot count on \"Spider-Verse\""
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 63730.0,
      "end_time": 67360.0,
      "text": "is two to three times higher than other animated films."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 67360.0,
      "end_time": 69110.0,
      "text": "Each year, animated films seem"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 69110.0,
      "end_time": 71620.0,
      "text": "to look more and more like real life."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 71620.0,
      "end_time": 74190.0,
      "text": "For \"Spider-Verse,\" instead of making the animation"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 74190.0,
      "end_time": 76620.0,
      "text": "photo-realistic, the creators wanted the movie"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 76620.0,
      "end_time": 80383.0,
      "text": "to stand out on its own as something new for viewers"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 81260.0,
      "end_time": 82920.0,
      "text": "just as they were being introduced to"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 82920.0,
      "end_time": 85840.0,
      "text": "a new Spider-Man in Miles Morales,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 85840.0,
      "end_time": 88460.0,
      "text": "while at the same time sticking as much as they could"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 88460.0,
      "end_time": 90899.0,
      "text": "to traditional print comic book style."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 90900.0,
      "end_time": 93907.0,
      "text": "As Head of Character Animation Josh Beveridge put it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 93907.0,
      "end_time": 97590.0,
      "text": "\"Don&#39;t emulate reality, and don&#39;t make it a cartoon.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 97590.0,
      "end_time": 99260.0,
      "text": "To accomplish this, they used a number"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 99260.0,
      "end_time": 101286.0,
      "text": "of different techniques that make"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 101286.0,
      "end_time": 103463.0,
      "text": "\"Spider-Verse\" a groundbreaking film."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 104670.0,
      "end_time": 108310.0,
      "text": "One of the most noticeable differences involves frame rate."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 108310.0,
      "end_time": 112900.0,
      "text": "Animated films are typically 24 frames per second,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 112900.0,
      "end_time": 114320.0,
      "text": "and creating a different image for each frame"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 114320.0,
      "end_time": 116470.0,
      "text": "is known as animating on ones."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 116470.0,
      "end_time": 118850.0,
      "text": "\"Spider-Verse\" broke the mold and animated"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 118850.0,
      "end_time": 121280.0,
      "text": "much of the movie on twos as well,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 121280.0,
      "end_time": 123240.0,
      "text": "meaning they kept some of the images on screen"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 123240.0,
      "end_time": 126199.0,
      "text": "for two frames, which makes the animation feel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 126200.0,
      "end_time": 129500.0,
      "text": "as the producers describe it, \"crunchy.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 129500.0,
      "end_time": 131600.0,
      "text": "Each character&#39;s pose lasts longer"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 131600.0,
      "end_time": 133313.0,
      "text": "and is much more pronounced."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 134340.0,
      "end_time": 137913.0,
      "text": "Like here, when Prowler is chasing Miles through the alley."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 139240.0,
      "end_time": 141790.0,
      "text": "You can see examples of animating on twos"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 141790.0,
      "end_time": 143810.0,
      "text": "in some of the original Disney films."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 143810.0,
      "end_time": 146230.0,
      "text": "The \"Spider-Verse\" animators alternated between"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 146230.0,
      "end_time": 150700.0,
      "text": "on twos and on ones depending on the nature of the scene."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 150700.0,
      "end_time": 154750.0,
      "text": "They could make Miles seem fast or skilled in some shots,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 154750.0,
      "end_time": 158820.0,
      "text": "on ones, and struggle in others, on twos."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 158820.0,
      "end_time": 161239.0,
      "text": "Sometimes he would be on twos"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 161240.0,
      "end_time": 163830.0,
      "text": "while other characters were on ones."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 163830.0,
      "end_time": 165550.0,
      "text": "When they&#39;re swinging through the forest,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 165550.0,
      "end_time": 168920.0,
      "text": "Miles is on twos because he&#39;s clumsy"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 168920.0,
      "end_time": 172273.0,
      "text": "while Peter B. Parker is on ones because he&#39;s more skilled."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 173320.0,
      "end_time": 176120.0,
      "text": "This subtly helped illustrate how Miles was slowly"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 176120.0,
      "end_time": 178740.0,
      "text": "becoming more comfortable with his powers."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 178740.0,
      "end_time": 180870.0,
      "text": "Each character&#39;s detailed animation style"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 180870.0,
      "end_time": 183470.0,
      "text": "helped to bring out his or her personality."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 183470.0,
      "end_time": 184859.0,
      "text": "Another major technique was how"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 184860.0,
      "end_time": 187300.0,
      "text": "they chose not to use motion blur,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 187300.0,
      "end_time": 189560.0,
      "text": "a CGI trick which most new films use"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 189560.0,
      "end_time": 193170.0,
      "text": "to soften a movement and make it seem more real."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 193170.0,
      "end_time": 196873.0,
      "text": "Instead, they used an old-school technique called a smear."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 197730.0,
      "end_time": 199920.0,
      "text": "This was used a lot in early cartoons"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 199920.0,
      "end_time": 201600.0,
      "text": "to create the sense of motion."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 201600.0,
      "end_time": 203440.0,
      "text": "If you look at a single frame,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 203440.0,
      "end_time": 205609.0,
      "text": "you&#39;ll notice things like multiple limbs"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 205610.0,
      "end_time": 207730.0,
      "text": "to create the illusion of movement."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 207730.0,
      "end_time": 210269.0,
      "text": "Here, Gwen is playing the drums,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 210270.0,
      "end_time": 213230.0,
      "text": "and you can see multiple hands and drum sticks."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 213960.0,
      "end_time": 217860.0,
      "text": "And here, when Miles has his cape ripped off his back."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 217860.0,
      "end_time": 218860.0,
      "text": "Miles Morales: I think it&#39;s cool."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 218860.0,
      "end_time": 220900.0,
      "text": "Peter B Parker: Spider-Man doesn&#39;t wear a cape."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 220900.0,
      "end_time": 222764.0,
      "text": "Narrator: You can see multiple arms in some frames."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 225540.0,
      "end_time": 228400.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s an example of one of the first cartoons"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 228400.0,
      "end_time": 231359.0,
      "text": "to use motion smearing, the 1942 short"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 231360.0,
      "end_time": 234730.0,
      "text": "called \"The Dover Boys at Pimento University.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 234730.0,
      "end_time": 237250.0,
      "text": "So those are some of the things they borrowed"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 237250.0,
      "end_time": 239360.0,
      "text": "from older animated films, but there&#39;s"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 239360.0,
      "end_time": 241670.0,
      "text": "plenty of new innovations too."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 241670.0,
      "end_time": 244100.0,
      "text": "Some things they borrowed from comic books,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 244100.0,
      "end_time": 245859.0,
      "text": "but we&#39;ve never seen them in a movie."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 246940.0,
      "end_time": 251100.0,
      "text": "Basically, the entire movie is a comic book that moves."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 251100.0,
      "end_time": 253480.0,
      "text": "Co-director Phil Lord said, \"If you freeze"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 253480.0,
      "end_time": 255679.0,
      "text": "any part of the movie at any time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 255680.0,
      "end_time": 257519.0,
      "text": "it will look like an illustration"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 257519.0,
      "end_time": 259669.0,
      "text": "with hand-drawn touches and all.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 259670.00000000003,
      "end_time": 261450.00000000003,
      "text": "There are even moments in the film"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 261450.0,
      "end_time": 264719.0,
      "text": "when hand-drawn still images pop up in the shots"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 264720.0,
      "end_time": 267500.0,
      "text": "to replace the computer animation."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 267500.0,
      "end_time": 269420.0,
      "text": "Like this shot, when Miles is running"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 269420.0,
      "end_time": 272403.0,
      "text": "through the streets of New York and he leaps off a taxi."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 273460.0,
      "end_time": 276650.0,
      "text": "And they layered 2D ink lines on top of the 3D art"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 276650.0,
      "end_time": 279352.0,
      "text": "to give the characters more of a hand-drawn look."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 281530.0,
      "end_time": 284100.0,
      "text": "If you look at a comic book, you may have noticed"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 284100.0,
      "end_time": 287260.0,
      "text": "a common error where the ink is misprinted."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 287260.0,
      "end_time": 289800.0,
      "text": "The filmmakers decided to use this misprint style"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 289800.0,
      "end_time": 292940.0,
      "text": "in the film to create a depth of field"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 292940.0,
      "end_time": 295300.0,
      "text": "instead of blurring the background."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 295300.0,
      "end_time": 296900.0,
      "text": "When something is in focus, the colors"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 296900.0,
      "end_time": 298400.0,
      "text": "align and are crisper."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 298400.0,
      "end_time": 300880.0,
      "text": "They used a technique called half-toning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 300880.0,
      "end_time": 304540.0,
      "text": "which uses dots to create colors and gradients."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 304540.0,
      "end_time": 308510.0,
      "text": "Shadows were created with hatching, or crisscrossed lines."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 308510.0,
      "end_time": 311340.0,
      "text": "Legendary Marvel artist Jack Kirby"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 311340.0,
      "end_time": 316340.0,
      "text": "was known for his abstract dots, or \"Kirby Krackle,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 316400.0,
      "end_time": 319800.0,
      "text": "which create the illusion of energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 319800.0,
      "end_time": 322690.0,
      "text": "The film references and uses the effect multiple times,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 322690.0,
      "end_time": 326540.0,
      "text": "when the portal opens and when Miles is spray-painting."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 326540.0,
      "end_time": 329500.0,
      "text": "There are action lines to show movement,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 329500.0,
      "end_time": 332100.0,
      "text": "and they used comics&#39; signature onomatopoeia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 332100.0,
      "end_time": 334390.0,
      "text": "or words on the image, to frequently"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 334390.0,
      "end_time": 336830.0,
      "text": "represent sounds and motion."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 336830.0,
      "end_time": 338490.0,
      "text": "Comic panels made out of webbing"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 338490.0,
      "end_time": 340870.0,
      "text": "show montages and background action."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 340870.0,
      "end_time": 343400.0,
      "text": "&#39;Cause there are six different spider-people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 343400.0,
      "end_time": 344919.0,
      "text": "they could also play with multiple"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 344920.0,
      "end_time": 347200.0,
      "text": "animation styles in one film."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 347200.0,
      "end_time": 350550.0,
      "text": "They actually studied manga, Japanese comics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 350550.0,
      "end_time": 353630.0,
      "text": "when designing the surface of the robot Spidey."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 353630.0,
      "end_time": 356880.0,
      "text": "Both Peni and Spider-pig have exaggerated anime"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 356880.0,
      "end_time": 359450.0,
      "text": "and cartoonish movements that stand out"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 359450.0,
      "end_time": 361159.0,
      "text": "compared to Miles&#39; world."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 361160.0,
      "end_time": 364790.0,
      "text": "CG supervisor Michael Lasker says Spider-Man Noir"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 364790.0,
      "end_time": 367200.0,
      "text": "was the most stylized character,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 367200.0,
      "end_time": 369320.0,
      "text": "and was an extra challenge since he was"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 369320.0,
      "end_time": 371200.0,
      "text": "drawn in only black and white"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 371200.0,
      "end_time": 373823.0,
      "text": "but required detailed textures and shading."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 375150.0,
      "end_time": 375983.0,
      "text": "Spider-Man Noir: Hey, fellas."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 376880.0,
      "end_time": 377969.0,
      "text": "Miles Morales: Is he in black and white?"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 377970.0,
      "end_time": 379378.0,
      "text": "Peter B. Parker: Where&#39;s that wind coming from?"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 379378.0,
      "end_time": 380211.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re in a basement."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 380211.0,
      "end_time": 382900.0,
      "text": "Narrator: Animator Nick Kondo tweeted that"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 382900.0,
      "end_time": 385780.0,
      "text": "this one scene involving all of the spider-people"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 385780.0,
      "end_time": 387950.0,
      "text": "was the most technically challenging for him,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 387950.0,
      "end_time": 390220.0,
      "text": "taking two months to get right."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 390970.0,
      "end_time": 393700.0,
      "text": "What each spider-person had in common"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 393700.0,
      "end_time": 395580.0,
      "text": "was that they were always kept low to the ground,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 395580.0,
      "end_time": 398100.0,
      "text": "forming acute angles with their limbs."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 398100.0,
      "end_time": 400900.0,
      "text": "The attention to detail is everywhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 400900.0,
      "end_time": 402719.0,
      "text": "Backgrounds like New York City&#39;s streets"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 402720.0,
      "end_time": 406220.0,
      "text": "were studied closely to get them as accurate as possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 406220.0,
      "end_time": 408180.0,
      "text": "And if you look closely, you can find"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 408180.0,
      "end_time": 411810.0,
      "text": "multiple Stan Lees inserted in certain frames."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 411810.0,
      "end_time": 414200.0,
      "text": "All of these techniques combined to make a movie"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 414200.0,
      "end_time": 416219.0,
      "text": "that has stood out among not just"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 416220.0,
      "end_time": 420653.0,
      "text": "the animated films of 2018, but perhaps of all time."
    }
  ]
}